<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-853-528  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 853 528.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Nov 6 1989 v23 n45 p86(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Lights-out does not leave Mervyn's in the dark. (Mervyn'sautomates data centers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ryan, Alan J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Mervyn's department-store chain uses robotics technology toautomate its data center in Hayward, CA.andP;  The five StorageTechnology Corp 4480 tape-library systems mount, eject and storetape cartridges without operator intervention, performing 23,000mounts and dismounts, and 3,00 enters and ejects weekly.andP;  It savesan estimated 300 man-hours per week and improves the workplaceenvironment by creating 'zones.' The tape and direct-accessstorage device areas are a darkened zone; humans do not have to do'command center' work in an unpleasant environment.andP;  Mervyn's isalso automating its printing room by converting two of itsprinters to roll-paper feed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mervyn's (automation).andO;Topic:     AutomationManagement of EDPRobotsDirect Access Storage Devices.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>